CORPUS NOTICE

The moral corpus of Protocol 1019 is derived from "The Spirits' Book"
(O Livro dos Espíritos) by Allan Kardec, originally published in 1857.
The original work is in the public domain.

The structured meta-principles, simulation tests, validation engine,
architectural decisions, doctrinal synthesis, and all original
contributions contained in this repository are original works authored
by Sérgio de Lima Filho and are covered by the proprietary license
above.

The corpus serves as a moral reference ontology. MAA makes no
theological claim. It declares structural consistency with the corpus.
